Since there are no spaces in between the <code><span></code> elements, I expect them not to wrap but all sit on the same line, which seems to be the case in all browsers    <code>span {
  position: relative;
}</code>  <code><span>Fooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooo</span><span>foo</span><span>Baaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaar</span><span>bar</span></code>    But when adding a <code>::before</code> tooltip element this behaviour changes. While they stay on the same line in Firefox (114), they start wrapping in Safari (16) and Chrome (114).    <code>span {
  position: relative;
}
span::before {
  content: 'tooltip';
  position: absolute;
  left: 0;
  top: 0;
  opacity: 0;
  background: grey;
  color: white;
  transition: opacity 100ms;
}
