  opacity: 100;
}</code>  <code><span>Fooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooo</span><span>foo</span><span>Baaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaar</span><span>bar</span></code>    Why is that and is there a way to prevent it?  Different <code>display</code> options on the <code>::before</code> elements didn't have an effect.  But I just noticed that setting <code>inline-block</code> on the <code>span</code> s actually seems to have the same effect as adding the <code>::before</code> element    <code>span {
