}</code>  <code><span>Fooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooo</span><span>foo</span><span>Baaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaar</span><span>bar</span></code>    Is there a logical explanation for the wrapping, or can this be considered unexpected behaviour?  Since in the real example there are whitespaces which should break, wrapping everything in a <code>white-space: nowrap;</code> container isn't an option.  Here's an example with whitespaces where <code>FoooooooBaaaaaaar</code> should stay together and not split into two lines    <code>span {
  position: relative;
}
