If you want to avoid setting an explicit width so you can style the background according to the actual length of the text, you can do the following:  Wrap your link:  <code> <p>To stay up to date <span><a href="#">Follow Us</a></span></p>
</code>  Note that I have added a <code><span></code> tag around the link.  Style your wrapper with CSS:  <code> span {
   display: inline-block;
