Below is the code I've used to solve this matter. Basically, using JS, we calculate the width of the container, and together with the width of the tabs (all tabs have the same width) calculate the number of tabs per row, and the remainder. Using a simple modulo comparison, we can then insert a <code>clear: both</code> style (forcing the tab to move to an empty row).  <code>var allTabs = $$('#tab-container li');
var tabNum = allTabs.length;
var tabWidth = allTabs[0].offsetWidth;
var oWidth = $('tab-container').offsetWidth;
var tabRowNum = Math.floor(oWidth/tabWidth);
var tabRowOffset = (tabNum % tabRowNum);
for(var i = 0; i < tabNum; i++) {
    if((i % tabRowNum) == tabRowOffset) {
        allTabs[i].setStyle('clear', 'both');
    }
    else {
        allTabs[i].setStyle('clear', 'none');
    }
}
</code>

